-- Czech Stocks: New World Resources, Utility CEZ Move in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-03-20T16:04:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/czech-stocks-new-world-resources-utility-cez-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell 0.6 percent to 992.6 at the close in Prague, snapping two
days of gains.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the country’s biggest power utility, slid
0.6 percent to 805.1 koruna. Electricity for next-year delivery
in Germany, where CEZ exports part of its output, dropped 1
percent to 52.20 euros per megawatt-hour.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the Czech Republic’s
biggest producer of coking coal, lost 2.4 percent to 129.30
koruna, its fourth day of declines. Stocks and commodities fell
worldwide amid signs economic growth is slowing in China, the
world’s largest energy consumer and steelmaker.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  